709627f-a.title: Manhattan: 7th Avenue South - Grove Street
709627f-a.text:
Seventh Avenue South, east side, and 76-70 Grove Street, at and south
of the Sheridan Sqquare subway station at West 4th Street. The
subway entrance is in a little island which used to be the N.W.
corner of Grove (formerly Burrows Street, originally Columbia Street)
and West 4th (formerly Asylum Street) Streets. Sheidan Square
(9.v.) is properly the triangular opcn space shown here in the left
background, but it is loosely applied to both sides of Seventh Avenue
South, from Christopher to Grove Streets, inclusive.
About 1928.
Ewing Galloway.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

720289f-a.title: Manhattan: Grove Street - 7th Avenue South
720289f-a.text:
Grove Street, southerly side, east from Seventh Avenue
South (right, not included), showing buildings there-
upon, as viewed across the open triangular park at
Christopher Street. In the center is the gap formed by
the convergance of Washington Place and West 4th Street,
and known as Sheridan Souare. The photographer details
the restaurant-bar of Jack Delaney in View 2. This ad-
joins the corner of Seventh Avenue.
June 6, 1940
No's. 1-2
P. L. Sperr
